cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with developing a new classifier system to tackle the problem of non-Markov environments. It involves machine learning techniques, such as reinforcement learning, and uses memory to store input sensation history. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control systems and decision-making, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
